  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large cazuela over medium heat.",
    "add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "add the caraway seeds and cook for 30 seconds.",
    "add the collard greens, diced red bell pepper, and bay leaves.",
    "cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "add the canned diced tomatoes and vegetable broth.",
    "season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "bring the stew to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the collard greens are al-dente.",
    "serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley if desired."
